section.section:
A person who issues, sells, or offers to sell a passenger ticket to board a vessel may not omit reference to the country of registry of the vessel in any advertisement or any other similar printed paper or notice, written or oral, regarding:
The voyage or the ticket that entitles or purports to entitle its owner, purchaser, or holder to the voyage;
The vessel for which the voyage is sold or offered;
The line that the vessel is part of; or
If applicable, that the person is an agent for the line or vessel.
